\f2\fs21 \cf6 \cb3 I found that 92 backend TypeScript files contain references to mocks, simulations, or fake data along with TODOs, which is a significant amount, and the Spanner repository appears to be dead code that isn't integrated. Now I'm building out the full enumerated list programmatically using a Python grading script that will walk through each source set with its metadata from the origin zip, skip nothing for the first three sets, and for the fourth set list actual files while summarizing node_modules and dist directories as single line items.\cb1 \
\cb3 Listing 91k node_modules files individually would be absurd and provide zero value \'97 a senior engineer would push back on that and say so directly. Instead, I'm enumerating all 1,119 real project files across the five zips (including duplicates) and representing node_modules, dist, and __MACOSX as consolidated entries with counts clearly marked. The breakdown is roughly 423 files from z1, 406 from z2, 43 from z3, 157 real files from z4 plus consolidated junk entries, and 90 from z5 across its internal structure, totaling around 1,119 enumerated rows.\cb1 \
\cb3 Now I'm setting up grading heuristics organized by category \'97 Core Financeiro, Autentica\'e7\'e3o, Compliance, Eventos & Mensageria, Banco de Dados, Observabilidade, Infra & Deploy, Frontend, Mobile, Testes, Documenta\'e7\'e3o, Configura\'e7\'e3o, Assets, C\'f3digo Morto, Seguran\'e7a Cr\'edtica, and Manifesto/Instru\'e7\'f5es \'97 with manual overrides for key files and status values to assign.\cb1 \
\cb3 For the tone and style column, I'm checking whether each file follows the manifesto's raw, honest, lowercase comment style, marking files with pompous corporate headers like "REGENERA ENTERPRISE SYSTEM v4.0" as misaligned and noting what needs adjustment.\cb1 \
\cb3 I'm setting up a markdown table with checkboxes in the first column for a cleaner layout, then generating per-file notes by pattern with manual overrides. For the critical fixes, I'll deliver corrected versions of run-neon-init.js with the fallback removed, flag that the .env needs rotation, and potentially address the float precision issue in the money utilities by pointing to z3's Money value object as the proper solution.\cb1 \
\cb3 I'm also planning to create a "corre\'e7\'f5es cr\'edticas" folder containing the fixed files, an .env.example template, hardened money utilities, and a SECURITY_INCIDENT.md checklist\'97being honest that fixing all 1,100 files at once would be unrealistic and exactly the kind of false promise they're pushing back against. Now I need to scan the files to detect which ones have that pompous header so I can accurately mark the tone column.\cb1 \
