\f2\fs21 \cf6 \cb3 I'm spotting a critical concurrency issue in the payment service\'97the balance check on the sender's ledger account reads the signed balance without acquiring a lock, which means two concurrent payments can both pass validation and cause a double-spend. I need to add row-level locking like\'a0
\f0\fs21\fsmilli10800 \cf21 \cb22 SELECT ... FOR UPDATE
\f2\fs21 \cf6 \cb3 \'a0or use an advisory lock to serialize access per account.\cb1 \
\cb3 There's also a timezone problem in the limits validation\'97it's using the server's local time instead of explicitly setting America/Sao_Paulo, and the daily window calculation in the database is probably UTC-based, so the BACEN nightly limits are misaligned with the actual Brazilian day. The EndToEndId generation looks acceptable per spec even with lowercase characters, though there's a minor modulo bias that's negligible. The\'a0
\f0\fs21\fsmilli10800 \cf21 \cb22 submit()
\f2\fs21 \cf6 \cb3 \'a0method updates the status to SENT without wrapping it in a transaction or verifying that rows were actually affected, which could leave the system in an inconsistent state if the settlement submission succeeds but the status update fails. The\'a0
\f0\fs21\fsmilli10800 \cf21 \cb22 hashRequest
\f2\fs21 \cf6 \cb3 \'a0function has a real bug \'97 using\'a0
\f0\fs21\fsmilli10800 \cf21 \cb22 JSON.stringify
\f2\fs21 \cf6 \cb3 \'a0with a replacer array that only includes top-level keys means nested objects get serialized incompletely, so different payloads could hash to the same value and cause false replay detection. Need proper canonicalization. Also, the interval string interpolation uses constants so it's safe from injection, but parametrizing would be cleaner. And I should verify that the app module's\'a0
\f0\fs21\fsmilli10800 \cf21 \cb22 'LOCAL_ONLY_CHANGE_ME'
\f2\fs21 \cf6 \cb3 \'a0secret fallbacks don't accidentally run in production.\cb1 \
\cb3 Now checking if the runtime-mode guard and env schema actually enforce that production rejects these placeholder secrets \'97 if they don't, that's a fail-fast vulnerability. Also need to look at main.ts to see if helmet and ValidationPipe are missing from the setup, and then audit the remaining files like rate-limit guard, permissions, session service, webhook verification, and migrations.\cb1 \
\
