\f2\fs21 \cf6 \cb3 I'm identifying the critical bugs that need fixing, starting with a double-spend vulnerability in the payment service where the account balance is checked without row-level locking\'97I need to add a\'a0
\f0\fs21\fsmilli10800 \cf21 \cb22 FOR UPDATE
\f2\fs21 \cf6 \cb3 \'a0lock on the ledger account within the same transaction to prevent race conditions. There's also an identity validation issue in the controller where user information is being read directly from headers without proper verification.\cb1 \
\cb3 For the headers problem, the honest fix is to require an active session token and validate it against the database to ensure the session belongs to the claimed user and that the account ownership is legitimate. The codebase doesn't have an accounts table yet, so I'm deciding between adding ownership validation to the existing migration or creating a new one\'97I'm leaning toward a\'a0
\f0\fs21\fsmilli10800 \cf21 \cb22 SessionAuthGuard
\f2\fs21 \cf6 \cb3 \'a0that validates the session first, then documenting that account ownership binding requires a future migration to avoid scope creep on what's already shipped.\cb1 \
\cb3 There's also a critical bug where\'a0
\f0\fs21\fsmilli10800 \cf21 \cb22 request.user
\f2\fs21 \cf6 \cb3 \'a0is never set, so the rate-limit policies for USER and ACCOUNT scopes silently degrade to IP-based limiting. The guard will fix both issues at once.\cb1 \
\cb3 The\'a0
\f0\fs21\fsmilli10800 \cf21 \cb22 IdempotencyService.hashRequest
\f2\fs21 \cf6 \cb3 \'a0replacer is dropping nested keys because it's only sorting top-level keys\'97I need recursive canonicalization instead.\cb1 \
\cb3 For the PIX submission flow, there's a race condition where if the settlement succeeds but the database update finds zero rows, the external ID gets lost. I need to wrap this in a transaction with row locking and validate the state transition. The timezone handling for daily limits is also wrong since it's using the server's local time instead of S\'e3o Paulo time.\cb1 \
\cb3 I should add a helper that enforces secrets at startup\'97in production and sandbox, it needs to fail immediately if an env var is missing or still set to the placeholder value.\cb1 \
\cb3 For the in-memory rate limiter issue, I need to gate the factory so it refuses to boot with an in-memory runner in production and requires Redis instead.\cb1 \
\cb3 On the idempotency race condition where\'a0
\f0\fs21\fsmilli10800 \cf21 \cb22 complete
\f2\fs21 \cf6 \cb3 \'a0throws ServiceUnavailable after the payment's already processed\'97that's genuinely an impossible state within the same transaction, so I'll keep it but add a clarifying comment.\cb1 \
\cb3 I also need to pull out the hardcoded\'a0
\f0\fs21\fsmilli10800 \cf21 \cb22 LEASE_SECONDS
\f2\fs21 \cf6 \cb3 \'a0and\'a0
\f0\fs21\fsmilli10800 \cf21 \cb22 TTL_HOURS
\f2\fs21 \cf6 \cb3 \'a0values that are interpolated directly into SQL queries and make them proper parameters for cleaner code.\cb1 \
\cb3 The\'a0
\f0\fs21\fsmilli10800 \cf21 \cb22 assertWithinLimits
\f2\fs21 \cf6 \cb3 \'a0function correctly doesn't count\'a0
\f0\fs21\fsmilli10800 \cf21 \cb22 FAILED
\f2\fs21 \cf6 \cb3 \'a0or\'a0
\f0\fs21\fsmilli10800 \cf21 \cb22 REVERSED
\f2\fs21 \cf6 \cb3 \'a0statuses, which is right.\cb1 \
\cb3 There's an import ordering issue in metrics.service where the Controller import comes after other code\'97I'll move it to the top for proper style.\cb1 \
\cb3 The webhook claim logic has a potential race: if an invalid signature gets recorded as REJECTED first, then the same event arrives with a valid signature later, the INSERT DO NOTHING will conflict with the existing REJECTED record and return it as a duplicate, leaving the webhook permanently rejected even though it's now valid\'97this could be an attack vector where an invalid signature blocks legitimate retries.\cb1 \
\cb3 I need to fix the ON CONFLICT clause to update the status back to PROCESSING and mark the signature as valid when a previously rejected claim comes through with correct credentials.\cb1 \
\cb3 For main.ts, helmet isn't in the dependencies, so I'll add basic security headers manually via a simple middleware without adding a new package.\cb1 \
\cb3 The\'a0
\f0\fs21\fsmilli10800 \cf21 \cb22 generateEndToEndId
\f2\fs21 \cf6 \cb3 \'a0uses UTC timestamps from\'a0
\f0\fs21\fsmilli10800 \cf21 \cb22 toISOString()
\f2\fs21 \cf6 \cb3 , but I need to check if BACEN expects Bras\'edlia time instead\'97the E2E ID timestamp might need adjustment.\cb1 \
\cb3 Now I'm going through the codebase to rewrite comments in the manifesto's style: lowercase, direct, confessional, technical, no fluff\'97keeping that honest, minimal tone throughout without overdoing it.\cb1 \
