\f2\fs21 \cf6 \cb3 The previous zip was just a cosmetic reskin with no actual improvements, so I'm starting fresh. I need to create the files one by one with real fixes and senior-level depth, writing each to the regenerabank-core directory, then validating with TypeScript and Jest before delivering the final package.\cb1 \
\cb3 Here's the file-by-file plan: the money value object gets tone refinements while keeping its solid API; state machines and ledger posting get tone work; idempotency service needs recursive canonicalization and parametrized intervals; the Pix payment service requires a double-spend lock, timezone handling, and transactional submission; the Pix controller needs session guard enforcement; I'm adding a new session auth guard that validates sessions and populates request.user; session service gets a validateActive method for the guard to use; permissions and auth controller get tone updates; rate-limit guard gets tone work and depends on request.user being set by the guard chain.\cb1 \
\cb3 For guard ordering, the session auth guard must run before rate-limit to populate the user, so I'll register it globally as a decorator-driven RequireSession guard that runs first in the app module. Runtime mode and HTTP exception filter get tone updates; the env schema needs refinements for secret validation in production, including checks for the IP_HASH_SECRET_REF and PIX_KEY_HASH_SECRET_REF variables; metrics service gets import reorganization and tone work; outbox dispatcher gets tone updates.\cb1 \
\cb3 Now moving through the webhook verifier to fix the rejected-burn conflict resolution logic, then tackling tone updates across reconciliation, AML structuring rules, privacy requests, consents, PIX entities, and provider contracts \'97 some of these files need their full content fetched before rewriting since I only have partial views.\cb1 \
\cb3 Continuing with health checks, tokens configuration, and the main app module where I need to fix secrets and Redis fail-fast behavior in production plus wire up the session auth guard, then securing main.ts with proper headers.\cb1 \
\cb3 For tests, I'm adding a canonicalization test to the domain foundation spec and sketching out a double-spend concurrency test for the ledger invariants using the existing postEntry helper and FOR UPDATE serialization.\cb1 \
\cb3 Then updating the README and bumping the version to 0.5.0, adding tone headers to migrations while keeping the SQL untouched, and writing a changelog section in the implementation notes. I need to read through the remaining files I haven't fully reviewed yet \'97 privacy, consent entities, pix entities, provider contracts, sandbox providers, and the spec files \'97 to complete the full picture.\cb1 \
